segment.source: The WPA Exporter is a command-line tool that provides WPA functionality for automated analysis scenarios.
segment.target: The WPA Exporter is a command-line tool that provides WPA functionality for automated analysis scenarios.

segment.source: By batching WPA Exporter commands together, you can perform trace analysis on a much larger scale than through the UI.
segment.target: By batching WPA Exporter commands together, you can perform trace analysis on a much larger scale than through the UI.

segment.source: You can use the WPA Exporter to export tables from a single trace and profile, optionally filtered to a specific time range, to a .csv (comma-separated values) file.
segment.target: You can use the WPA Exporter to export tables from a single trace and profile, optionally filtered to a specific time range, to a .csv (comma-separated values) file.

segment.source: These time ranges can be defined by one of the following:
segment.target: These time ranges can be defined by one of the following:

segment.source: If you do not specify a time range, data from the entire trace duration is exported.
segment.target: If you do not specify a time range, data from the entire trace duration is exported.

segment.source: You cannot currently export tables from Comparative Analysis Views.
segment.target: You cannot currently export tables from Comparative Analysis Views.

segment.source: To use the WPA Exporter, you must provide an existing trace file along with a profile.
segment.target: To use the WPA Exporter, you must provide an existing trace file along with a profile.

segment.source: A trace file that contains the data to export.
segment.target: A trace file that contains the data to export.

segment.source: A WPA profile (.wpaProfile) that contains the tables to export.
segment.target: A WPA profile (.wpaProfile) that contains the tables to export.

segment.source: (Optional) The character to use as the separator between values in the CSV.
segment.target: (Optional) The character to use as the separator between values in the CSV.

segment.source: The default separator is a comma.
segment.target: The default separator is a comma.

segment.source: (Optional) A string to prepend to each of the output filenames.
segment.target: (Optional) A string to prepend to each of the output filenames.

segment.source: (Optional) The folder to which the tables will be exported.
segment.target: (Optional) The folder to which the tables will be exported.

segment.source: (Optional) The time span, from start to end, to be exported.
segment.target: (Optional) The time span, from start to end, to be exported.

segment.source: The default unit is nanoseconds, but you can also specify seconds (s), milliseconds (ms), or microseconds (us).
segment.target: The default unit is nanoseconds, but you can also specify seconds (s), milliseconds (ms), or microseconds (us).

segment.source: (Optional) The range to be exported, as specified by two named markers.
segment.target: (Optional) The range to be exported, as specified by two named markers.

segment.source: (Optional) One or more manifest files that contain regions of interest.
segment.target: (Optional) One or more manifest files that contain regions of interest.

segment.source: You can specify this flag without the flag to export the entire Regions of Interest table.
segment.target: You can specify this flag without the flag to export the entire Regions of Interest table.

segment.source: (Optional) The name of a specific region in the trace.
segment.target: (Optional) The name of a specific region in the trace.

segment.source: Use this flag to export data only for the duration of the region.
segment.target: Use this flag to export data only for the duration of the region.

segment.source: If you use this flag, you must also specify at least one regions of interest manifest file.
segment.target: If you use this flag, you must also specify at least one regions of interest manifest file.

segment.source: (Optional) Include this flag to enable symbol loading.
segment.target: (Optional) Include this flag to enable symbol loading.

segment.source: (Optional) Process the trace even in the presence of time inversions.
segment.target: (Optional) Process the trace even in the presence of time inversions.

segment.source: The output file names are automatically generated based on the table and preset names.
segment.target: The output file names are automatically generated based on the table and preset names.

segment.source: The user may optionally specify a prefix () and directory ().
segment.target: The user may optionally specify a prefix () and directory ().
